<br>
One, the guildchat was too much swearing, juvenile behavior, the guild leader and officers promoted that behavior. I left and about 2 weeks later, guild was gone (I suspect a guildwipe took care of it).<br>
<br>
Another, more tragic story was the confluence of 4 hard knocks that together did the guild in, any one or maybe 2 and the guild could have survived. 1 - Leader quit EQ. 2 - Personality conflicts over a trouble-making player, some folks wanted him in, some did not, lot of tension and guild evenly divided about the issue. 3 - Really bad raid in Droga, bad wipe out, some folks left, others logged out, I ended up hiring a necro to come several zones to summon bodies with my funds (about half the guild quit after that event). 4 - A bug in High keep was /guildremoving folks as they zoned in, the guild-leader and all the officers were removed at once. GMs could not invite anyone nor promote anyone unless they were in the guild, so it was a slow death after that. The 4th one was the final blow, the only option was to get all the members online and recreate the guild, folks just went on their way. <br>
<br>
I am a lot more picky about guilds now. I scope them out long and hard to see if we are a good fit. <p><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64195'>Combat Profile</a><br>
<a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64207'>Tradeskill Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/2/02 6:46:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17930.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Have you been in a guild that died?</span><hr size=1> On the Zek's, the guilds have all the difficulties listed here, as well as the everpresent accusations of dishonorable PVP, 'so and so didnt Loot and Scoot', 'so and so Corpse Camped me', 'so and so is immortal healing'.....<br>
<br>
I've seen a lot of guilds on Vallon split over the following disagreement:  So and so officer is really nice and helps the guild out a lot, giving gear to the bank and recruiting and powerleveling.  Then this officer loses their temper and is caught doing something against the guilds PVP charter.   The guild leader removes them to ensure the reputation of the guild as being honorable, then half the guild leaves because they support the officer in question for being such a nice person and helping them get gear or levels.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, if you don't guildremove people who break the honorable play charter, you eventually end up with a bad reputation for the guild, and unless you can beat up every other guild on the server, they will be hunting you and your members.  This happened in a guild I was in early on (Bloodletter's Bane) ... they decided to start a war with the Shanks (who outnumbered and outgunned them) over a personal vendetta, and weren't using play nice policies in the war.  I decided to move on, and I think its safe to say that they were eliminated by the Shanks, as any time a member tried to log on they were killed.<br>
<br>
Its a full time job fielding complaints (real or imaginary or accidental) about PVP stuff in a guild on Vallon Zek. <p>Obon Took, Amazon Mother
